00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:44,760
So this is a very standard scenario.

220
00:14:44,760 --> 00:14:50,920
The rat learns to press the lever to get the reward, and that's sort of very well understood.

221
00:14:50,920 --> 00:14:56,600
But the interesting thing is that the rat is really a collection of cells, and no individual

222
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:59,000
cell has both experiences.

223
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:02,720
So there are cells on the foot of the rat that interact with the lever.

224
00:15:02,720 --> 00:15:08,440
There are cells in the intestine that collect the nutritious reward sometime later.

225
00:15:08,440 --> 00:15:13,000
But no individual cell has the experience of doing this and receiving that.

226
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:18,360
And so who is it that owns this kind of associative memory between two events that no individual

227
00:15:18,360 --> 00:15:19,360
cell experienced?

228
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:24,160
So clearly, you need some sort of a, and the standard answer, of course, is the nervous

229
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:29,720
system provides this, you need some sort of way to integrate individual cellular activities

230
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,720
towards a single being.

231
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,600
