00:48:52,120 --> 00:48:53,720
This is cytoskeletal bending.

799
00:48:53,720 --> 00:48:55,720
This is a single cell bending around itself.

800
00:48:55,720 --> 00:48:56,840
So look what's going on here.

801
00:48:56,840 --> 00:49:01,320
Different molecular mechanisms are being called up in the service

802
00:49:01,320 --> 00:49:03,240
of a high-level anatomical goal.

803
00:49:03,240 --> 00:49:05,880
This is what's known as top-down causation.

804
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:10,200
In the service of a particular anatomical goal, different molecular mechanisms

805
00:49:10,200 --> 00:49:13,720
can be called up.

806
00:49:13,720 --> 00:49:18,760
So this ability to adjust to circumstance has to do with external circumstances,

807
00:49:18,760 --> 00:49:21,400
like being injured or being cut in half or losing a limb,

808
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:23,240
but also internal circumstances.

809
00:49:23,240 --> 00:49:26,200
Not only can't you count on your body maintaining a particular shape,

810
00:49:26,200 --> 00:49:27,720
you can't even count on your own parts.

811
00:49:27,720 --> 00:49:30,680
You have no idea what size your cells are going to be when you come into the world

